This paper presents a tool for learning embeddings of words and entities from Wikipedia, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and linguistics. 

The paper also mentions downstream NLP models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these categories often deal with text data and feature extraction. 

Additionally, the paper mentions that the tool uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DL (Machine Learning and Deep Learning), which focus on the development and application of AI and deep learning models.
